{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow Any Motorcycle to Be Safely Restricted to 35kW for A2 Riders",
        "additional_details": "Current A2 rules limit riders to fewer motorcycles \u2013 those up to 35kW or, with a fitted restrictor, up to 70kW \u2013 reducing choice and sometimes forcing illegal riding, which increases risk. Modern restriction systems can safely limit any bike to 35\u202fkW, giving riders access to more motorcycles and safer technology like ABS and traction control. Updating the law will expand legal options and could help encourage responsible riding, support skill progression, and protect all road users.",
        "background": "We want the Government to allow motorcycles of any original power to be safely restricted to 35\u202fkW for A2 riders, removing the \u201cdouble power\u201d rule. All restrictions should be verifiable and meet safety standards, giving riders more choice, freedom, and safer progression.",
